<h1 style="color:#002859;">About</h1>

 <p text-align:justify>My name is Ziang Yan (&#x989C;&#x5B50;&#x6602), a PhD student in physics at <a href="http://www.phas.ubc.ca/" target="_blank">Department of Physics and Astronomy, University of British Columbia</a>. I'm working with <a href="https://www.phas.ubc.ca/users/gary-hinshaw" target="_blank">Prof. Gary Hinshaw</a> and <a href="http://www.phas.ubc.ca/~waerbeke/" target="_blank">Prof. Ludovic van Waerbeke</a>.</p> 
<p> My work focuses partly on cross-analysing different large-scale structure tracers to probe properties of galaxy clusters and large-scale structures of the universe. I'm also interested in probing properties of galaxy clusters with cosmoligycal hydrodynamic simulations (e.g. BAHAMAS) and machine learning. The other part of my work involved with the CLASS telescope which is now measuring the polarized CMB signal to reveal the mystery of cosmological inflation.</p>
<p><b>Contact me</b>: yanza15 at phas.ubc.ca </p>    
